    "name": "Question 13 @ 2016/2017 @ Electrostatics",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Two charges Q₁=25µC and Q₂=50µC are located at positions R₁=3jm and R₂=4im. Find the force on Q₁ due to Q₂.",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "1.8i - 1.3j N",
        "9i - 6.8j N",
        "9i - 6.8j × 10⁻¹² N",
        "None of the above"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "None of the above"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Step 1: Distance vector</b><br>• \\(\\vec{r} = R₂ - R₁ = 4\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j}\\)<br>• Distance \\(r = \\sqrt{4^2 + 3^2} = 5\\,m\\)<br><br><b>Step 2: Calculate force</b><br>\\(\\vec{F} = k\\frac{Q_1 Q_2}{r^3}\\vec{r}\\)<br>\\(\\vec{F} = (9\\times10^9)\\frac{(25\\times10^{-6})(50\\times10^{-6})}{125}(4\\hat{i} - 3\\hat{j})\\)<br>\\(\\vec{F} = 0.36\\hat{i} - 0.27\\hat{j}\\,N\\)<br><br>None of the options match this result."
    },
    "topic": [
      "Physics",
      "Electromagnetism and Electrodynamics",
      "Electrostatics",
      "Coulomb's Law",
      "Mathematical Methods for Physics"
    ]
