      "type": "string",
      "content": "20.37 × 10⁶ A/m² (Note: Correct answer not listed; closest is (b) 19.6 × 10⁷ A/m²)"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "<b>Step 1: Convert units</b><br>• Current \\(I = 4\\,mA = 4 \\times 10^{-3}\\,A\\)<br>• Diameter \\(d = 0.5\\,mm = 0.5 \\times 10^{-3}\\,m\\)<br><br><b>Step 2: Calculate cross-sectional area</b><br>\\(A = \\pi \\left(\\frac{d}{2}\\right)^2 = \\pi \\left(0.25 \\times 10^{-3}\\right)^2 = 1.96 \\times 10^{-7}\\,m^2\\)<br><br><b>Step 3: Current density</b><br>\\(J = \\frac{I}{A} = \\frac{4 \\times 10^{-3}}{1.96 \\times 10^{-7}} \\approx 20.37 \\times 10^6\\,A/m^2\\)<br><br>None of the options match exactly. The closest is (b), but it’s off by a factor of 10."
